text:
kekerasan seksual terhadap perempuan adalah kejahatan universal. tidak hanya endemis tetapi juga pervasive dan berulang-ulang terjadi dimana-mana dalam kurun waktu yang sangat panjang. di balik suburnya kekerasan seksual terhadap perempuan adalah disebabkan budaya patriarki yang menyebabkan diskriminasi dan ketidakadilan dalam masyarakat. ketidakadilan dalam masyarakat dapat kita lihat dari praktik perlakuan hak istimewa terhadap laki-laki. sejak kecil laki-laki diajarkan agar mepunyai sifat yang berani, kuat, tangguh sehingga sifat tersebut selalu ingin mereka tampakkan kepada siapapun. sifat kejantanan yang dimilki oleh laki-laki seolah-olah menjadi kebanggaan yang mereka dan diekpresikan dalam bentuk antara lain pelecehan terhadap perempuan.

kekerasan seksual terhadap perempuan mustahil untuk dihentikan apabila keadilan sulit ditegakkan. apabila budaya patriarki senantiasa direproduksi dan dilanggengkan baik oleh individu, keluarga, masyarakat, serta negara yang dikemas dan disosialisasikan melalui undang-undang, maka diskriminasi akan tetap berlaku dan menimbulkan ketidakadilan, baik berupa kekerasan maupun tindakan yang lainnya. kuncinya adalah, kekerasan seksual dapat dihentikan jika masyarakat dan negara dapat menghentikan ketidakadilan dan menghapus budaya patriarki.

sumber : jurnal perempuan
poster by : hanny shonia

because for some of us women, shame has so strongly gripped our vocal cords that it takes weeks, months, years to even say a word. and when that occurs, man or woman, your responsibility is not to question the validity of the assault.
and yes, #metoo

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like â€˜drain the swampâ€™ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the â€˜deep stateâ€™ that werenâ€™t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

thatâ€™s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him â€œwe can take it.â€ no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but itâ€™s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then itâ€™s easy to come along for the ride. thereâ€™s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. theyâ€™re both just characters on the television.

thatâ€™s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. itâ€™s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. itâ€™s that weâ€™ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
six years ago today i came out as gay. my parents' response was to try and arrange a marriage to a woman as a â€œcureâ€. my abusive ex-boyfriend tried - and failed - to get a court to take down my coming out video in which i spoke about the abuse i endured from him. 
i wish i could say that coming out is a magical panacea. that you just say the words youâ€™ve been keeping secret and bottled up and all will be well. but after the all social media likes and the â€œiâ€™m so proud of youâ€ comments, the challenges which made it hard to come out are still there. only the luckiest of us can come out without a hitch.

for the rest of us, itâ€™s a journey that often gets worse before it gets better. my journey was one of a lot of loss. some family no longer speak to me. some places i cannot visit again. sometimes i wonder where my career could have been if i just stayed in the closet and avoided all of this. 
but, looking back, i can definitely say that iâ€™m in a better place today than i was on the day that i came out. self-care alone was not enough. this christmas i want to thank all those who stuck by me through all the ups and downs these years out of the closet has brought me.

have a merry christmas and happy holidays! ğŸ„â¤ï¸ #gay #gaymuslim #comingout #metoo #holidays

text_retweet:
#repost @ashley_with_restoring_heart ãƒ»ãƒ»ãƒ»
if you grew up in a family of abuse, and the abuser(s) are still there, then staying away from being with family over the holidays can be one of the most difficult decisions to make and stick to.
.
for some, holidays were the only "good times" - meaning, the only times when abuse wasn't taking place. thus, it's very easy for a survivor to glorify the holidays into this magical space where it's as if the abuse never existed, and also believe that the family you experience on that day is the only reality. but, unfortunately, the truth is that image is the furthest thing from reality.
.
this can be especially difficult to wrap your mind around if the abuse has occurred since you were a child. your brain's understanding of the world and family, was forming in the midst of these abusive relationship(s).
.
#traumabonding is a common thing to develop in those environments. even though you may be in a place today where part of you knows what your abuser(s) have done (or are doing) is wrong, you can still find yourself confused and tied to this idea that you are supposed to be with them over the holidays.
.
this makes the decision to stay away all the harder and so confusing.
.
my assault was not by a family member, but i have worked with survivors who that is their story. some are able to clearly see their abuser(s) for who they are, and others find it confusing to see them clearly.
.
abuse is about having power over someone else. it's about control. taking steps to physically distance yourself is so important to break that power, but so is emotional and mental distance.
.
survivors who have been able to break trauma bonds often say the turning point was when they decided to let the "dream" die of what their relationship with their abuser(s) could be. dreams that one day they'll stop, apologize, all will be okay.
.
**see the 2 comments below for the rest of this post**
.
 #sexualabuse #childabuse #unsafe  #familyabuse #sexualtrauma #metoo #survivor

text:
yes! yes! yes! photo shared from @sophia.rewilding my thoughts: i am a true believer in the healing that comes when we adopt the internal family systems model. it breaks my heart when i see so many well meaning people in positions of authority (coaches, trainers, mentors, educators etc.) advising others to ignore, tell off or get aggressive with their inner critics; to show 'em who's boss! ğŸ˜¢ everything i've learned about how we actually heal, grow and thrive says the exact opposite. that that sort of badass approach can actually do more damage in the long run. ğŸ¤”
i try to actively practice self-compassion every day. i am really working on consciously responding to my inner child, my inner critic, and every other part of me with respect, kindness and empathy. i can already see a huge shift. i only started learning about internal family systems three months ago but it has already been a real game changer. it has allowed me to understand that behaviours i would have once shamed myself over were only developed to protect me. knowing this, i can stop the shaming and replace it with unconditional love. it's not easy and i certainly have a long way to go but the wheels are in motion and for that i am truly grateful. ğŸ’–
